      "Design involves: <br /> - achieving goals within constraints and trade-off between these<br /> - understanding the raw materials: computer and human<br /> - accepting limitations of humans and of design<br />",
      "The design process has several stages and is iterative and never complete.",
      "Interaction starts with getting to know the users and their context: <br /> - finding out who they are and what they are like ... probably not like you!<br /> - talking to them, watching them<br />",
      "Scenarios are rich design stories, which can be used and reused throughout design: <br /> - they help us see what users will want to do<br /> - they give a step-by-step walkthrough of users' interactions: including what they see, do and are thinking<br />",
